  sleep
  Builtin Function



      [1mSynopsis[0m
        Put RLaB to sleep.

      [1mSyntax[0m
        sleep ( [4msleepval[24m )

      [1mDescription[0m
        Sleep is an interface to the POSIX.1 sleep system function. The
        argument, [4msleepval[24m specifies the time in seconds the process
        should sleep for. Observe, non-integer values are allowed as
        well.

        The return value is either zero or the number of seconds left to
        sleep (if the sleep has been interrupted).















































